description:
&lt;p&gt;Lewisham and Greenwich NHS Trust are looking for a motivated Nurse or Midwife that enjoys finding solutions and supporting teams deliver high quality care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting new post has been established to join our busy corporate nursing workforce team as the Safe staffing lead nurse/midwife. This is an excellent opportunity to demonstrate your values and passion for delivering care, as well as your project management skills as the Trust continues to implement and roll out the safer nursing care tool and build the redeployment potential of Health Rostering and Safe Care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work alongside the Associate Chief Nurse and the current non clinical Health Roster team to support the heads of nursing/midwifery and matrons with staffing reviews. This will include attending the safe staffing operational meeting, reviews of the nursing establishment and reviewing the use of the Health Roster and SafeCare systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants will need to have had experience and some knowledge of the Health Roster system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Amanda Rolland amanda.rolland@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
